Program: Crossing Continents
Title: Malaysia: Racial Supremacy No More?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00gdjvc
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 18 May 2009
For nearly four decades, ethnic Malays have benefited from positive discrimination over Malaysians of ethnic Chinese and Indian origin - which make up nearly 40 percent of the population. But in 2008, the country's unique racial compact began to be strongly challenged from within. Mukul Devichand reports on the tensions and meets Malay, Indian and Chinese young people on the front lines of the struggle between ingrained racism and the possibility of a more equal future. Show less